dc_title_s: Reconnoissance map of the United States showing the distribution of the geologic system so far as known
dc_description_s: Relief shown by contour lines. In upper border: U.S. Geological Survey. Fourteenth annual report, pl. II. Shows Indian reservations. Includes legend. Scale approximately 1:7,000,000. Compiled from data in possession of the U.S. Geological Survey by W.J. McGee, 1893.
